attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, Intel 80386, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a malicious botnet client, specifically a variant of the Gafgyt (BASHLITE) or Mirai families, targeting Linux IoT architectures. It exhibits characteristic C2-controlled behaviors including DDoS attack execution (SYN, ACK, UDP, ICMP, GRE, and HTTP flooding) as evidenced by command strings like '!syn', '!ack', and '!udpcustom' in function sub_804c854. Function sub_804a7f8 performs aggressive process scanning via /proc to identify and terminate competing botnet processes, while sub_8049550 implements an anti-analysis check by querying /sys/class/dmi/id/product_name for 'VMware'. The binary also contains logic for daemonization, persistence, and uses hardcoded HTTP User-Agent strings for application-layer attacks.
